<headline>Winter Storm Watch issued December 26 at 3:49PM MST until December 28 at 8:00AM MST by NWS Saltlake</headline>
<description>...WINTER STORM WATCH IN EFFECT FROM MONDAY AFTERNOON THROUGH
TUESDAY MORNING...
* WHAT...Heavy snow possible. Total snow accumulations of 4 to 8
inches, with higher amounts possible near the east entrance
tunnels on SR-9. Winds could gust as high as 40 mph.
* WHERE...Zion National Park.
* WHEN...From Monday afternoon through Tuesday morning.
* IMPACTS...Travel could be very difficult to impossible.</description>
<instruction>Monitor the latest forecasts for updates on this situation.</instruction>
